I have often spoken of the light within the soul, which is uncreated and eke
uncreaturely.  It is this light I am so often hinting at in my discourses, it
is the light which lays straight hold of God, bare and unveiled, as he is in
himself; that is to say, it catches him in the act of self-begetting.
